-- American Stabbed Outside U.S. Embassy in Egypt, Police Say
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2013-05-09T15:39:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-09/american-stabbed-outside-u-s-embassy-in-egypt-police-say.html
An American man was stabbed outside
the U.S. Embassy in Cairo, a security official said, the latest
inciden of deteriorating security in  Egypt .  The victim was transferred to a nearby hospital, head of
Cairo’s Qasr El-Nil police station, Hany Girgis, said by phone.
An Egyptian man was arrested and is being held in custody, he
said. The motives for the assault weren’t immediately clear.  Egypt has been plagued by a rise in crime, a proliferation
of weapons, vigilante killings and sexual attacks, more than two
years after the fall of President  Hosni Mubarak .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  